# =============================================================================
# AZURE_CREDENTIALS_STAGING — example reference
# =============================================================================
#
# This file documents the value that should be pasted into the GitHub secret
# named `AZURE_CREDENTIALS_STAGING` (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# → Secrets → New repository secret).
#
# The staging deploy workflow (.github/workflows/wc-staging-deploy.yml) uses it
# in every `azure/login@v2` step:  `creds: ${{ secrets.AZURE_CREDENTIALS_STAGING }}`.
# It is the legacy service-principal credentials JSON. (Day-2 upgrade: switch to
# OIDC / federated credentials and drop this secret — see DEPLOYMENT.md.)
#
# DO NOT COMMIT REAL CREDENTIALS TO THIS FILE.
# =============================================================================
#
# === HOW TO MINT IT ===
#
# 1. Create a service principal scoped Contributor on the STAGING resource group.
#    The `--json-auth` output IS the value you paste (older az CLI: `--sdk-auth`).
#
#    az ad sp create-for-rbac \
#      --name "github-actions-wc-staging" \
#      --role Contributor \
#      --scopes /subscriptions/65a4056e-681d-44cb-9d47-3eb3a9c77d94/resourceGroups/rg-wc-staging-ch-north \
#      --json-auth
#
# 2. Grant image push on the SHARED registry `acrwc` (it lives in a different RG):
#
#    az role assignment create \
#      --assignee <clientId-from-step-1> \
#      --role AcrPush \
#      --scope /subscriptions/65a4056e-681d-44cb-9d47-3eb3a9c77d94/resourceGroups/rg-wc-infra-shared-ch-north/providers/Microsoft.ContainerRegistry/registries/acrwc
#
# 3. Paste the ENTIRE JSON from step 1 as the secret value. Shape:
#
# {
#   "clientId": "<app-registration-client-id>",
#   "clientSecret": "<generated-secret>",
#   "subscriptionId": "65a4056e-681d-44cb-9d47-3eb3a9c77d94",
#   "tenantId": "<azure-ad-tenant-id>",
#   "activeDirectoryEndpointUrl": "https://login.microsoftonline.com",
#   "resourceManagerEndpointUrl": "https://management.azure.com/",
#   "activeDirectoryGraphResourceId": "https://graph.windows.net/",
#   "sqlManagementEndpointUrl": "https://management.core.windows.net:8443/",
#   "galleryEndpointUrl": "https://gallery.azure.com/",
#   "managementEndpointUrl": "https://management.core.windows.net/"
# }
